Kalisha Naicker Queen Blose: The bail is too low. The mother needs to pay for all the resources she wasted. Everyone was out looking for the child. She does not deserve the baby. Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories THE Upper Highway community was outraged when the Durban Magistrate s Court granted Baby Siwaphiwe s mother and her lover R1 000 bail, after staging the child s kidnap. According to police sources there were many inconsistencies in investigations and police eventually set up a roadblock in Mariannhill where three people, including the 34-year-old biological mother of the baby, another woman, and a man, were arrested. The Fever asked people what they thought of the situation. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.